      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Male orc deadwatcher chieftain",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> Deadwatcher chieftain (A10) — son of a Rotten Tongue war chief, holder of the post a record three years, inordinately proud of the stuffed nightbelly boa on his ceiling. <strong>Tactics:</strong> on an alarm he joins the bows at A8, grows impatient within a few rounds, and <em>leaps off the parapet</em> (@Check[type:acrobatics|dc:15] to break the fall) to get at melee. Eager to fight something other than wild animals; fights to the death, pursues relentlessly — <strong>but never into Scarwall</strong>. The tribe can also be talked past: @Check[type:intimidation|dc:28] or @Check[type:diplomacy|dc:32] (or a duel/worthy gift) buys passage. <strong>Treasure:</strong> Akeraum (a dragon-feller — +1 striking greatsword), his necklace of seven silver-plated red-wyrmling skulls (~105 gp), 10 pp and 6 gp in pouch.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
